OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1773076274
OL,3,CPort Vale reach FA Cup quarter-finals
OL,4,Cfor first time in 72-years
OL,6,FPort Vale fans are celebrating one of
OL,7,Fthe club's best ever days by defeating
OL,8,FPremier League side Sunderland to
OL,9,Freach the quarter finals of the FA Cup
OL,10,Ffor the first time in 72 years.
OL,12,FNew Zealand international midfielder
OL,13,FBen Waine scored the only goal for
OL,14,FVale, who are bottom of League One, to
OL,15,Fcomplete the incredible upset.
OL,17,FPort Vale will find out who their
OL,18,Fopponents are in the quarter-final on
OL,19,FMonday night (March 9). If they win
OL,20,Fthat game, they will play in the FA
OL,21,FCup semi-finals at Wembley.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/5
